  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis predictions were benchmarked against published experimental datasets; the primary methodological reference underpinning the power-law hemolysis model adopted here is the 2024 review by Fraser et al. (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), which consolidates current best practice for blood damage index computation in rotary blood pumps.",
