    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Discretization error GCI of 3.1% and output comparison error of 8.4% are within acceptance criteria. The hemolysis model methodology, anchored in the power-law formulation reviewed in the primary reference, has been independently validated against FDA benchmark data. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model adequately identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
